Job Description:
The Access to Care Program (ATC) is responsible for the IM/IT initiatives that support the Ontario Wait Time Strategy and the Patient First Act. ATC manages the Wait Time Information System (WTIS) which captures wait times for surgical data from facilities across Ontario. ATC also oversees the Surgical Efficiency Targets Program (SETP) which supports the measurement and reporting of Operating Room performance across the province. This information is used by the Ministry of Health and Long-Term Care (ministry), Local Health Integration Networks (LHINs)/regions, facilities, and other stakeholders to inform performance improvement strategies for reducing wait times and improving efficiencies for surgical services in Ontario.

The Senior Business Analyst (SBA) role for Surgery is responsible for supporting the Surgical Information Program and the Group Manager within Access to Care at Ontario Health. The SBA will work closely with a team of other analysts, clinicians, and key stakeholders to support management of high-profile provincial projects. The SBA will perform key issues analysis with efficient and effective coordination of business processes and utilizing both the surgical wait time and surgical efficiency data sets.
Here is what you will be doing:

Support complex projects with key partners and stakeholders;
Provide business analysis on key issues and related processes using both quantitative and qualitative data.
Provide quality assurance review on team work with attention to detail when reviewing materials;
Developing and enhancing business process maps and related methodologies.
Performing assignments and special projects in support of departmental objectives, often developing and assisting in implementation of solutions to unique or highly complex business problems;
Responding to business inquiries, creating reusable inquiry documentation, and keeping documentation updated related assigned projects or initiatives.
Here is what you will need to be successful:

Education and Experience

Bachelor’s degree in Health Informatics, Business, Computer Science or related discipline, or equivalent experience is required;
Minimum five years of business experience required (e.g. a role on an information technology project, collaborating with stakeholders, or experience working in a hospital setting with clinicians);
Demonstrates strong knowledge of advanced analytics techniques including statistical analytics;
Subject matter knowledge within surgical wait times and efficiencies in Ontario, and national/international trends and best practices is an asset;
A Masters level degree in one of the above disciplines is an asset.
Advanced knowledge of Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, Project, Visio, MS Teams and Excel required.
Experience in collecting/documenting information related to operational and performance reporting;
Experience collecting and documenting business processes and information flows;
Attributes

Ability to work under pressure and manage multiple tasks and deadlines required;
Strong communication, both written and verbal, comprehension and listening skills;
Demonstrated knowledge and use of business analysis methodologies and tools;
Highly organized with the capacity to prioritize and complete multiple tasks effectively;
Ability to work with minimal supervision and is an effective team member and contributor;
Must be team-oriented, possess a positive attitude and work well with others;
Employment Type: Permanent full-time 37.5 hours
